                <h2>The Illusion of Top-Line Revenue</h2>
                <p>We are culturally trained to look at the biggest number on the screen. In the gig economy, this is the "Weekly Earnings" screenshot.</p>
                <p>A viral screenshot might show <strong>$533 in a single Sunday</strong>. It looks like executive pay for entry-level work. But this is an accounting error.</p>
                <p>It confuses <strong>Revenue</strong> (Money in) with <strong>Profit</strong> (Money kept). In a business, this mistake leads to bankruptcy. In a career, it leads to burnout.</p>

